      <title>Remote unlocking</title>
      <link>https://blog.billy.sh/post/remote-unlocking/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 10 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hi@billy.sh (BOFH)</author>
      <guid>https://blog.billy.sh/post/remote-unlocking/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;is-your-data-safe&#34;&gt;Is your data safe?&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When you have the &lt;strong&gt;good habit&lt;/strong&gt; of encrypting &lt;strong&gt;every&lt;/strong&gt; disk you use, it&amp;rsquo;s not always as easy as entering the password or unlocking it with a physical device.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;What happens if you encrypt your home-lab (without a monitor) or a remote server that you don&amp;rsquo;t have access to?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Well we need early access to the server, &lt;a href=&#34;https://matt.ucc.asn.au/dropbear/dropbear.html&#34;&gt;Dropbear&lt;/a&gt; to the rescue, installing that &amp;ldquo;&lt;em&gt;mini ssh server&lt;/em&gt;&amp;rdquo; inside &lt;strong&gt;initrd&lt;/strong&gt; does the trick.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
